##############################################################################
Pre-requisites for building the controller from source
##############################################################################
Note: You can skip installation of pre-requisites if already installed.

1. Follow steps given in pre-requisites_README on kubernetes master.

2. Run below command from terminal inside the source directory

   mvn package

3. On build success, you can find the executable binary in the "bin" folder

##############################################################################
Installation of binary on kubernetes master machine
##############################################################################
Pre-requisites
Kubernetes cluster should be up and running

STEPS:
1. Create cit_k8s_extensions folders in /opt of k8s master machine.
   Copy the binary to /opt/cit_k8s_extensions/bin folder 
	
    cp  citk8scontroller-1.0-SNAPSHOT /opt/cit_k8s_extensions/bin/.
	chmod +x /opt/cit_k8s_extensions/bin/citk8scontroller-1.0-SNAPSHOT

2. Create tag_prefix.conf file in /opt/cit_k8s_extensions/bin/ of k8s master machine with below json.

	{
		"trusted":<<prefix for trust tag>>
	}

3. Place below systemd service file in /etc/systemd/system/ folder (available in the same directory as this README)
		citk8scontroller.service

4. Run below commands to enable service daemon
	systemctl daemon-reload  #(to activate newly added service)

5. Run the custom controller using below command	

	systemctl start citk8scontroller.service

6. To check status of this service run below command
	
	systemctl status citk8scontroller.service

7. To stop this service run below command
	
	systemctl stop citk8scontroller.service

